    129128,"The Sandman Cometh!", 16348,"A family stumbles across a hostile alien made of sand. The military are helpless but it is defeated by the family’s bookish son who uses water to dissolve it and traps it in a bucket.",NULL,"Narrated in the first person. This story is divided into two untitled parts (6 pp 7 pp). Job number from Tom Lammers and Ger Apeldoorn via the Atlas/Timely discussion group.Story is pages 3-7 10-14 16-18 of comic (pages of story numbered 1 to 13).",19);
